title: Iceye introduces Dwell imaging mode
summary: Iceye unveiled an imaging mode at the GEOINT Symposium that distinguishes human-made from natural objects and highlights moving vehicles.

title: Rocket Lab ready to launch final TROPICS mission from New Zealand
summary: Just under three weeks after Rocket Lab launched the “Rocket Like a Hurricane” mission placing two time-resolved observations of precipitation structure and storm intensity with a constellation of smallsats (TROPICS) satellites for NASA into low Earth orbit, the company is set to launch its Electron rocket on the “Coming to a Storm Near You” mission.  Launching from Launch Complex 1B (LC-1B) on the Mahia Peninsula in New Zealand, this mission will place the final batch of TROPICS satellites into orbit.

title: Impulse and Relativity target 2026 for launch of first Mars lander mission
summary: Two companies are preparing for a 2026 launch of what they believe will be the first commercial robotic Mars lander mission, the start of what the companies plan to be a regular series of such missions.

title: Fleet Space secures $33 million for mineral exploration constellation
summary: Fleet Space Technologies has raised around $33 million in a Series C round to expand its satellite-based mineral exploration services.

title: NASA, Department of Education Partnership Strengthens STEM Education
summary: NASA and the U.S. Department of Education signed a memorandum of understanding on Wednesday, strengthening the collaboration between the two agencies, including efforts to increase access to high-quality STEM and space education to students and schools across the nation.

title: BlackSky, Spire roll out space-based maritime tracking service
summary: BlackSky and Spire Global announced May 24 they are offering a new monitoring service that tracks ships via satellites.

title: No one should be surprised Virgin Orbit failed—it had a terrible business plan
summary: The business case simply did not close.

title: Japan’s GITAI raises $29 million for space robotics business
summary: Japanese space robotics venture GITAI has raised around $29 million to accelerate technology development and its U.S. expansion plans.

title: Missile-warning satellite passes preliminary design review
summary: A U.S. missile-warning satellite completed a major review, keeping the spacecraft on track for launch in 2028.

title: Internet from a small satellite in geostationary orbit? Sure, why not
summary: "We now have a new way of connecting very remote places."
